    {
      "num": 2,
      "name": "Volume Engine",
      "tagline": "More Work. Less Rest. Real Growth.",
      "weeks": "Weeks 6–10",
      "startDate": "2026-05-28",
      "endDate": "2026-07-01",
      "focuses": [
        "Increase hypertrophy volume per muscle group with higher training density and shorter rest periods.",
        "Advance core loading from bodyweight to stability-based variations and introduce structured conditioning blocks."
      ],
      "message": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "You proved something in the first five weeks — you can show up, follow a structure, and get stronger doing it. Now the training has to change because you have.",
          "Cycle 2 is built around one principle: more work in less time. Rep ranges go up, rest periods come down, and every session should feel noticeably denser than what you were doing before. This is where your body is forced to adapt — not just neurally, but structurally. Muscle tissue has to grow to keep up with the demand.",
          "Your job is the same as Cycle 1: own every rep, log every set, and trust the process."
        ],
        "outcomes": [
          "Visible changes in upper body size and shape",
          "Significantly more comfort and confidence under the bar on leg days",
          "Noticeable jump in work capacity — sessions that would have buried you five weeks ago will feel routine",
          "Improved RPE calibration and tempo discipline across all movements"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 3,
      "name": "Metabolic Override",
      "weeks": "Weeks 11–16",
      "focuses": [
        "Shift training toward high-density supersets and circuit-based resistance work to maximise energy expenditure while preserving muscle.",
        "Peak direct abdominal volume and introduce advanced anti-extension progressions."
      ],
      "teaser": {
        "subtitle": "The volume you built becomes the fuel.",
        "paragraphs": [
          "Cycle 3 changes the rules entirely. The volume you are building now becomes the fuel for a training style designed to strip body fat while keeping every kilogram of muscle you have earned.",
          "Sessions will move faster, rest will shrink further, and the intensity will test a version of you that does not exist yet. This is the phase where the six-pack stops being a goal and starts becoming visible.",
          "What you build in these five weeks determines whether your body is ready for what comes next."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 4,
      "name": "Strength Reclaim",
      "weeks": "Weeks 17–21",
      "focuses": [
        "Restore and surpass Cycle 1 strength levels with reduced volume and higher intensity to protect lean mass through the deepening deficit.",
        "Reduce conditioning volume, refine muscular detail through isolation and contraction-focused work."
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": 5,
      "name": "The Reveal",
      "weeks": "Weeks 22–26",
      "focuses": [
        "Maintain peak strength, reduce fatigue accumulation, and bring body composition to target condition.",
        "Transition to a maintenance caloric intake; stress-test the physique and habits that will sustain results long-term."
      ]
    }
  ],
